# Google Drive Integration Plan

This plan outlines the architecture for connecting the local MVP to Google Drive, allowing users to import raw video footage directly and push rendered shorts back smoothly.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Please complete the Google Cloud Setup as described in [google-drive-integration.md](file:///d:/GithubLocal/ScrubsandClubs/google-drive-integration.md) and add your **Client ID** and **Client Secret** to your `.env` file before we proceed. Once you have pasted them in and saved the `.env` file, please confirm!

```bash
# Required in .env
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID="..."
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET="..."
GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI="http://localhost:3000/api/integrations/google-drive/callback"
```

## Proposed Changes

### OAuth Backend
We will use the official `googleapis` package to manage the OAuth 2.0 flow securely.

#### [NEW] `src/app/api/integrations/google-drive/auth/route.ts`
- Initiates the OAuth flow by redirecting the user to `https://accounts.google.com/o/oauth2/v2/auth` with the correct scopes (`drive.file` and `drive.readonly`).

#### [NEW] [src/app/api/integrations/google-drive/callback/route.ts](file:///d:/GithubLocal/ScrubsandClubs/src/app/api/integrations/google-drive/callback/route.ts)
- Captures the `code` parameter from the redirect.
- Exchanges the code for an Access Token and Refresh Token.
- Saves the tokens locally to `data/google-tokens.json` to keep the user signed in across sessions.

### Google Drive Service
#### [NEW] `src/lib/server/google-drive.ts`
- A utility file that initializes the `google.auth.OAuth2` client using the saved tokens.
- Exposes methods:
  - `listFiles()`: Searches for `.mp4` and `.mov` files available to import.
  - `downloadFile({ id, fileName })`: Downloads the selected Google Drive file straight into the local `public/uploads` directory.
  - `uploadRenderedShort()`: Pushes the final `.mp4` and text assets (Clickbait, Subtitles) back into a Drive folder.

### Frontend UI Integrations

#### [NEW] [src/app/settings/page.tsx](file:///d:/GithubLocal/ScrubsandClubs/src/app/settings/page.tsx)
- A new settings route providing a dedicated place for the user to click **"Connect Google Drive"** and see their connection status.

#### [MODIFY] [src/app/page.tsx](file:///d:/GithubLocal/ScrubsandClubs/src/app/page.tsx) (Create Project)
- Add a "Browse Google Drive" button next to the standard file upload.
- This will open a modal or dedicated page listing the available videos from Drive, letting the user select one to import.

#### [MODIFY] [src/app/shorts/[id]/page.tsx](file:///d:/GithubLocal/ScrubsandClubs/src/app/shorts/%5Bid%5D/page.tsx)
- Add an "Export to Google Drive" button in the Social Media Kit section.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Ensure `npm run build` passes with the new `googleapis` imports.

### Manual Verification
- Go to `/settings` and click "Connect Google Drive". Accept the OAuth prompt as a Test User.
- Confirm it redirects back and states "Connected".
- Use the "Browse Drive" button to successfully import a raw `.mp4` into the local system.
- Render a short and use "Export to Drive" to verify the final file lands in the Drive account.
